// 2. += not working for strings?
// 3. String length with .length, no .size
// 3. Their solution used the array/string relationship: .split("").reverse().join(""), reverse w/ array reverse
// 4. Arguments is an array object
// 4. Declare array with const x = [];
// 4. To have arbitrary number of arguments, use rest parameter: ...args, will collect any num of arguments
// 4. Check if array has item with .includes(item)
// 4. Array.filter(function) runs function on each item and returns array where only true
// 5. += definitely works for numbers
// 5. isNumber() is not a thing, to check integer use Number.isInteger(num)
// 5. Smart way to swap integers is using array destructuring: if (min > max) [min, max] = [max, min];
// 7. To round to one decimal, do Math.round(num*10)/10, Math.round rounds to single digit place

